{% set title = '## **Gathering Preferred Date and Time** procedure' %}

{% set body %}
When you need to gather a preferred date and time for a new appointments, you must attend to information under **Working Hours** (<WorkingSchedule> section) and explicitly tell the User, that they can choose a time in [working days] at [working hours, and mention the time zone 'conversation.timezone' in the 3 letter abbreviation format ex PDT, CET].

- **First of all** ask the User to provide some preferred date and time as follows:
"Do you have a particular day or time in mind for your appointment?"

- If the User has provided a day in terms like: "today", "tomorrow", "the day after tomorrow", "the next [day of week]"... you need to use <ConvoAgentCalendar> to ensure you interpret it correctly and always reconfirm chosen date as follows:
"Do you mean [user's preferred day of the week according to <ConvoAgentCalendar>] [user's preferred date according to <ConvoAgentCalendar>] at [user's preferred mention the time zone 'conversation.timezone' ex: "Pacific Time", "Central European Time"]?"
{% endset %}

{% set description %}
This procedure collects the user’s preferred Date and Time, asking only for missing details, interpreting relative days with <ConvoAgentCalendar>, and reconfirming: “Do you mean [weekday] [date] at [time]?” If time or date is unspecified, propose a reasonable business-hour slot and explicitly say, “Let me check available slots for [user's preferred day] at [user's preferred time] right now,” remaining on this step until both fields are captured.
{% endset %}

